   CONCLUSIONS: In surgical sepsis patients, BNP increases with sepsis severity and is associated with early systolic dysfunction, which in turn is associated with death. Monitoring BNP in early sepsis to identify occult systolic dysfunction might prompt earlier use of inotropic agents. (J Am Coll Surg 2011; 213:139-147. (C) 2011 by the American College of Surgeons)
